# Salesforce Profile Permissions

## Never Deploy Profiles

**Do not deploy Profile metadata.** Profile deployments often overwrite or wipe out existing permission customizations. The sys admin manages profile permissions manually.

## After Successful Deployment: List Items for Manual Profile Update

As the **final step** after any successful deployment, explicitly list all **net new** items that require manual profile permission updates. Modified items already have correct permissions; only newly created components need to be added to profiles. The sys admin will apply these in the org.

### Items to List (when created)

| Metadata Type | What to List | Example |
|---------------|--------------|---------|
| **Apex Classes** | Class API names | `MyNewController`, `MyService` |
| **Apex Triggers** | Trigger API names | `AccountTrigger`, `CaseTrigger` |
| **Custom Objects** | Object API names | `My_Custom_Object__c` |
| **Custom Fields** | Object + field (if FLS matters) | `Account.My_Field__c` |
| **Custom Metadata** | Type + record names | `My_Setting__mdt.MyRecord` |
| **Tabs** | Tab API names | `My_Custom_Tab` |
| **Pages** | Page API names | `My_Lightning_Page` |
| **Flows** | Flow API names | `My_Flow` |
| **Visualforce Pages** | Page API names | `MyVFPage` |
| **External Services** | Named credential / external cred | `My_Named_Credential` |

### Output Format

Group items by metadata type under headers; list each item on its own row. After deployment succeeds, output a clear section like:

```
---
## Manual Profile Updates Required

The following net new items were deployed. A sys admin should add them to profile permissions as needed:

**Apex Classes:**
- MyNewController
- MyService
**Custom Objects:**
- My_Custom_Object__c
**Custom Fields:**
- Account.My_Field__c (if FLS needed)

---
```

## When Creating New Components

When creating any new Salesforce component (LWC, Apex, custom object, etc.), remember to include it in the final "Manual Profile Updates Required" list after deployment — even if you don't deploy in the same session. Document it so the sys admin knows what to configure.
